Gyro city.... I was driving for a food delivery company and I walked into this place famished but I had 0 dollars to spend so i just called out the order for pick up and waited patiently. I couldnt help but scan the menu above and I grabbed my stomach to silence the hunger pains knowing I couldnt solve them, I looked at the door and thought I need air the food smell is killing me and before I could make my first step.. a gentleman from behind the counter said to me " hey come here I want you to try something" i replied I'm sorry sir I cant I'll just take the order for delivery and go.. he smiled and he put a box together with chicken and fries made a small honey mustard cup and put it in my hand. His warm smile reassured me he knew I was so hungry and I said to him please how much so I can pay you when I come back I'm always here for pick ups he said "I know but I'm not worried about the money, eat and go work I see you all the time and you're always moving" I held the box closer grabbed the order and went to my car..  I took a bite.. a little chicken and fries on the fork dipped in the honey mustard AND BOOM I shed a legit TEAR. The kindness of that man, the food was so good I went back when I wasnt working and I purchased 2 more to see if it was just a moment you know you're so hungry anything taste good... NOPE that's not the case here ... The chicken well seasoned cooked to supremacy and the fries... WOW with their own light buttery flavor it compliments the chicken even after the last bite 😍 thank Gyro City

Opa!!! Gyro City is in my opinion is the best fast food Gyro maker in Boston. Close to Fenway Park I find often times coming here for a pregame Gyro and then walk to the Red Sox game.  Lovers of the Gyro sandwich with fries stuff inside as sold in the villages of the Greek Isles are made that way here so you've found the place that will put craving to rest. Each Gyro is stuff with fries & tyitszicki , lettuce & slices of tomato on a fresh pita. Mixed with those ingredients will be some sorta roasted flesh of your choice or a souvlaki stick ( chicken or pork ) to accompany those fixings inside the pita. The other Gyro meat is the lamb/beef combo swirling giant meat posts roasting for the gentleman to shave it off for your sandwich. Outside of that there's a few more items including salad and soup for ordering but the main item aka the rock star item is the Gyro Sandwich.  Feta fries are a nice tasty accompaniment to your order should you want more fries.
